      "items": {
        "1": "The agent must carry and use their UIP card whenever performing their professional duties.",
        "2": "The agent commits to providing correct, clear, and verifiable information to clients.",
        "3": "The agent must present transparent and previously defined price tables to clients.",
        "4": "The agent must inform the client in advance of any relevant information necessary for completing the real estate transaction.",
        "5": "It is strictly prohibited for the agent to accept or request bribes, illegal payments, or any illicit benefits while performing their duties.",
        "6": "Any fraud or attempted fraud will be immediately reported to the competent authorities and may result in suspension or cancellation of the agent’s UIP indefinitely.",
        "7": "The agent or intermediary must fully comply with the rules, regulations, and guidelines established in the Guidebook for Agents and Intermediaries on the platform.",
        "8": "The agent or intermediary has the right to refuse service to any citizen, provided there are justifiable reasons and the refusal is not based on discrimination such as race, gender, religion, nationality, or sexual orientation.",
        "9": "Commissions related to the sale or intermediation of properties must be previously agreed upon between the parties involved in the transaction, namely the property owner and the agent or intermediary.",
        "10": "Any situation not covered in these terms or in the Agent and Intermediary Guidebook will be analyzed and handled according to the current legislation of the Republic of Angola."
      }
    },
